        "description": "Reset password using the verification code received via email.\n\n**Request Body:**\n- email (string, required): Valid email format - the email that requested the reset\n- code (string, required): 6-digit verification code from email (e.g., \"583921\")\n- newPassword (string, required): Minimum 8 characters\n\n**Response:**\n- message (string): Success message\n\n**Security Features:**\n- Validates email + code combination (code must belong to the email)\n- Validates code exists, not expired, and not used\n- Marks code as used after successful reset\n- Password is BCrypt encoded before storage\n- Automatically revokes ALL refresh tokens (forces re-login on all devices)\n- Code can only be used once\n- Code expires after 60 minutes\n\n**Validation:**\n- Code format: Must be exactly 6 digits (pattern: ^\\\\d{6}$)\n- Email format: Must be valid email\n\n**Error Cases:**\n- 400 Bad Request: Invalid, expired, or already used code\n- 400 Bad Request: Code does not match email\n- 400 Bad Request: Password too short (< 8 characters)\n- 400 Bad Request: Invalid email or code format\n\n**Post-Reset Actions:**\n- User must login again with new password\n- All active sessions are invalidated\n\n**Use Case:** User enters the 6-digit code from email along with their email and new password"
      },
