        },
        "description": "Complete worker signup using an invitation token. Creates worker account with associated company.\n\n**Request Body:**\n- invitationToken (string, required): UUID invitation token from email\n- email (string, required): Worker email (must match invitation email)\n- name (string, required): Worker's full name (2-100 characters)\n- username (string, required): Desired username (3-20 characters)\n- password (string, required): Password (minimum 8 characters)\n\n**Response:**\n- workerId (long): Created worker ID\n- name (string): Worker's name\n- email (string): Worker's email\n- username (string): Worker's username\n- companyName (string): Associated company name\n- message (string): Success message\n\n**Business Logic:**\n- Validates invitation token (must be valid, not expired, not already used)\n- Token expires after 7 days from invitation creation\n- Email in request must match invitation email\n- Creates User account with WORKER role\n- Creates Worker entity with name and company association\n- Marks invitation as used\n- Username must be unique across the system\n- User UUID is auto-generated\n\n**Security Features:**\n- Token-based verification ensures worker is invited\n- Email verification prevents token hijacking\n- Password is BCrypt encoded before storage\n- Token can only be used once\n- Invitation status updated to ACCEPTED on success\n\n**Status Code:** 200 OK\n\n**Error Responses:**\n- 400 Bad Request: Invalid or expired invitation token\n- 400 Bad Request: Invitation already used\n- 400 Bad Request: Email does not match invitation\n- 400 Bad Request: Invalid validation (name, username, password format)\n- 409 Conflict: Username already exists\n- 404 Not Found: Company not found or archived\n\n**Use Case:** Worker receives invitation email with token, creates account using this endpoint"
      },
